reviews.text: This is a beautiful place. Loved the ambience its very romantic and beautiful. brbrThen their food brWe ordered kaftani dahi kebab, coriander water chestnut  corn wonton fried and penne white sauce pasta. The drinks are also very nice, they even specially, modified the drinks as per our request.brbrAnd then the show stopper - TIRAMISU . One of the best tiramisu authentic I have had in Delhi. reviews.author: Saquib Khan
reviews.text: Nestled away in the quiet locale of Sainik Farms, Cabo is a chic restaurant with great ambience for indoor seating and a picturesque outdoor seating both covered inside a gazebo and open with ample plants and fountain to add to the glam quotient of this place. reviews.author: Janavi
reviews.text: been to Matteo as a regular. just the perfect spot for having your personal time with some decent beverages and simple finger food. brThis place hosts seating that are well places, you can have the privacy you want and also have the comfort of personal space. brbrThe staff needs a mention. I have seen several worry about the service, I see no problem, and if I did face any, its just a matter of asking then for anything. Courteous staff, disciplined and considerate. it takes little to no effort to speak with kindness to anyone, show this to them, they will even have a smile on their face while serving to you. brover all...brambience- 4.5 because its spacious, points taken away because Id prefer it to be a little more lit up. brfood - 4.5 limited simple menu, points taken away because some of their menu has frozen items.brservice - 5 no complaints brwashroom hygiene - 4.0 can have better locks and better placement of tissues.brparking - available brbudget friendly and serves the purpose of a cafe.

reviews.text: A place with very nice ambience to spend some leisure time in the evening. The chairs are very comfortable and deserve special mention. reviews.text: Nice ambience and snacks here is served in good quantity. We tried their shakes and it was really yummy.. This place has nice atmosphere and we will visit this place again for some nice coffee and snacks

reviews.author: Vivek Viswanathan
reviews.text: Matteo cafe reminds you of a cafe in California, San Mateo. The logo outside is inviting on the glass building. When you enter you get the enticing fragrance of coffee and you should find a seat on the red loveseat and make yourself comfortable, because the food and drinks will in fact ease into your mind. The cold coffee is a must for first timers which is topped off with a rich sweet cream swirl. The shakes are also very good and the chocolate shake is a personal favourite. the prices are reasonable and inclusive of taxes so you pay what you see, which is an added bonus with clarity. the service can be slightly better but its worth the wait !brEdited20-05-2020  I had visited Matteo lately and realized, the service has in fact been improved and hospitable, hence my update with the ratings! Everything else remains as, is or could be better. The cafe has infact caught up with the COVID times!!

reviews.author: Soorej Gopi
reviews.text: HOT CHOCOLATE WITH WHIPPED CREAM - thats the stuff dreams are made of!brbrThough I didnt get that for this visit, its my go to drink! I got the hazelnut latte and loved it! On a side note - theres sugar in the latte, do not add again! Yeah, I messed up and had to drink coffee payasam.brbrThe chairs are cozy, service is great and a good selection of food! Musics a little too loud, but thats not a problem.brbrGet a chair facing the road, sip on your hot chocolate and get some work done!

reviews.text: Why - This is a general hang out place for me. Always the first preference.brWhat I liked - the place sets your mood right for good conversations. The staff are really good.brWhat I loved - their Soya milk replacement on request.brPlatter winner - Date shakeratobrbrNo complaints cafe

You can sit, talk have good time.. the music is a bit moody.. and dont be surprised if suddenly you are staying to soft hymn and next instant feel like disco floor.

reviews.author: Rahul V
reviews.text: Simply Mindblowing Coffea and sandwich makes this place a 1 of a Kind.brMake sure you try their Shekerato Cold coffe with bloended Ice cream with No extra Sugarbrthis is where you should b especially on a weekday.brThey hold a specialty of having all couches to urself and u can sit until the universe ends. All food and drinks are very tasty and aromatic.brVery much Pocket friendly.

reviews.author: Megha Sreeram
reviews.text: So this was my first visit to Matteo in Indiranagar. I had been to Matteo on Church Street and loved the food there. So decided to check the one in Indiranagar as well. I wasnt disappointed at all.brbrWe ordered a hot cocoa, a Hawaiian Coconut Shekerato, an omelette sandwich, a chicken tikka sandwich and a plate of French fries. The food was excellent. The sandwiches were so good that I was filling yet felt light on the tummy. The fries were also fresh and not oily. The beverages were great too.brbrWhat I loved the most though is the laid back ambiance of the cafe. I mean there are a lot of cafes which are named cafes but we feel stressed even after spending considerable time inside. But Matteo was perfect and it was very relaxing to spend time there.br

reviews.author: Anju Gopal
reviews.text: Love this place. Went with family and enjoyed coffee and the time spent together. Awesome ambiance. Friendly staff. And good food and coffe.br

reviews.author: Debalina Gupta
reviews.text: Situated right off 12th Main, Indiranagar, this resto-pub turned out to be a delightful spot for lunch. The cocktails were absolutely spot onkudos to the bartender! The Picante specials, in particular, were exceptional.brbrIn the mood for starters, we ordered the beef carpaccio, salmon ceviche, pork arancini, and fish tacos. From the very first bite, I was blown away by the burst of flavors on each platetruly impressive!brbrAs for the service, Ralph was outstanding, recommending some incredible cocktails that perfectly complemented our meal.brbrThe cherry on top? By the time we stepped out, the valet was already waiting with my car. They informed us about this thoughtful service while we were settling the billa wonderful touch that truly elevated the experience.brbrAll in all, a fantastic visit. Im eager to return, try more of their cocktails, and soak in the evening ambiance. Highly recommended!

reviews.author: Laurent Moglia
reviews.text: I recently dined at Los Cavos in Bangalore and had an incredible experience! The small plates were absolutely fantastic  each dish was bursting with bold, fresh flavors. The fusion of Peruvian and other influences created a unique dining experience, with highlights like the ceviche and the empanadas that had just the right amount of crunch and flavor.brbrWhat truly set the evening apart, though, was the exceptional service from Ralph. He was attentive, knowledgeable, and offered great recommendations, which made the whole experience even better. Its rare to find service that feels both personal and professional, and Ralph definitely made us feel like valued guests.brbrThe ambiance was relaxed yet stylish, perfect for both a casual meal or a special occasion. Los Cavos is a gem in Bangalore, and Ill definitely be coming back for more. Highly recommend it!

reviews.author: Sahil Sanjeev
reviews.text: My first visit to Los Cavos last evening was an outstanding experience. From the warm welcome provided by Cassy and the attentive staff, to the delicious fish taco appetizer which I highly recommend, every aspect of the evening was fantastic. The eclectic selection of alcoholic beverages further enhanced the dining experience followed by a fun party. A special thank you to Cassy for making my visit truly memorable.

reviews.author: Mainak
reviews.text: Los Cavos brings a refreshing slice of Peruvian charm to the bustling streets of Indiranagar. Nestled amidst the citys chaos, stepping inside feels like entering a different world altogether. The interiors are stunningly designed, exuding warmth and elegance while paying homage to the rich Peruvian culture.brbrI had the Chicken Picante, and it was delightful. Perfectly spiced with just the right kick, it balanced flavor and heat masterfullydefinitely a dish that showcases the vibrant palate of Peruvian cuisine.brbrThe ambiance here is as inviting as the food. Its more than just a resto-bar; its an experience. Whether youre here for a relaxed meal or an evening drink, Los Cavos makes sure you leave with fond memories. If youre in Indiranagar, this is a must-visit for a unique culinary adventure.

reviews.author: Yash Solanki

reviews.author: Akshansh
reviews.text: Jamming Goat in Indiranagar is a fantastic spot for a night out! The ambiance is vibrant, with great music and a lively crowd. The food is exceptionaleach dish is thoughtfully crafted, with bold flavors and a unique twist. Their cocktails are equally impressive, perfectly balanced and creatively presented.brbrThe service was top-notch, with the staff being friendly and attentive. Whether youre looking for a casual evening with friends or a special celebration, Jamming Goat is a must-visit. Highly recommend trying their signature dishes and cocktails!

reviews.author: Soumya Gopi
reviews.text: I recently had a fantastic lunch at Jamming Goat 3.0 in Indiranagar, and its easily one of the best spots Ive tried recently. This buzzing place checks all the boxes good vibes, great grub, creative drinks loved my French 75, amazing service, and a stunning garden-like ambience.brbrHeres what stole the show for mebr Blue Pea  Truffle Cream Cheese Dim Sumbr Crispy Broccoli Poppers with Avocado and Wasabi Moussebr Spicy Tuna Rollbr Dantu Soppu Ratatouille Poppers with Rasam Chutneybr Malaysian Chicken Satay with Spicy Peanut SaucebrbrSpecial thanks to Chris, who guided us to the perfect dishes and drinks. I cant wait to go back.

reviews.author: Muqeet Khan
reviews.text: This place is perfect for some good times. The service is exceptional, the food and ambience was perfect. Every dish was really flavourful and my favourites were the sushi, dimsums ans the sheek. You would definitely visit here and I would suggest that you come in a bit early since its always packed.

reviews.author: Gurpreet Singh
reviews.text: The ambience is really good. Cecilia was a good host

reviews.author: Roopa Dey
reviews.text: It was a very enjoyable experience. Everything ordered was super yum! The passion fruit golgappa was too good, and the cheesecake was delicious! The flavors from all that we ordered were definitely there. The flavors were unique and kept us guessing similar tastes from different dishes weve tried before. My friends also mentioned that the chicken goli kabab was amazing. The wild mushroom and truffle pizza was equally good, but sorry, no photos as we ate it too fast! Absolutely happy with the Jamming Goat 3.0!brbr

reviews.author: Anupriy Kanti
reviews.text: This is my second visit and all the things I tried were amazing! brbrStarting off with Prawn Pepper Fry with Curd Rice Foam  this was a highly recommend dish and it was pretty good  unique. The other dish was the Char Pork Gao was also very tasty and definitely worth it if one is craving for some good dimsums. brbrThe two cocktails were also pretty memorable  Missionarys Downfall turned out to be a recreation of a 1930s drink and was a great drink while KFG was one the tastiest drinks I have had also it had a very Christmassy vibe. All in all, Jamming Goat 3.0 is becoming one of my regular hangouts and I cant wait to try more stuff here.

reviews.author: Satyajit Sutradhar
reviews.text: This is a wonderful place. The ambience is good and the food is really awesome. I loved the vibe. Korean chicken sushi and Malaysian chicken satay is a must try. Thanks to all our servers for their quick response.

reviews.author: Gautham Nedungadi
reviews.text: Absolutely love Jamming Goat. Couldnt recommend this place enough. Lets break the experience downbrbrFood brilliant. 1010. We had the prawn tempura sushi, peri peri chicken, papad platter, serradura which was just the best one weve ever had brbrAmbience perfect setting for a date or even a chill night with friends. They know how to set the mood.brbrMusic even though there isnt a dance floor, you cant help but groove! Superb choice. Again, they know how to set the mood. brbrService best in Bangalore weve experienced. Friendly staff and they clearly enjoy what they do! The vibe is infectious.brbrOverall if we could rate this place 65, we would

reviews.author: Nawab
reviews.text: Right from the hostess to the final server! Everybody was smiling, friendly and professional and we enjoyed the service! The food and the drinks are amazing! Their menu is really eclectic and the cocktails were fabulous! Loved our visit and will surely come again with friends and family! Keep it up guys.

reviews.author: Deepaboli
reviews.text: A Delightful Culinary Experience at Jamming Goat!brbrJamming Goat in Indiranagar is an absolute gem for food lovers! From the moment you step in, the cozy and chic ambience sets the tone for a memorable dining experience.brbrWhat I Lovedbr- Blue Pea Dimsums Stunning presentation and a burst of flavors.br- Crispy Broccoli Poppers Perfectly paired with avocado and wasabi mousseunique and addictive.br- Classic Sushi Beautifully plated and absolutely delicious.br- Linguine with Prawns The chorizo crumbs add a delightful crunch, making this pasta a standout dish.br- Deconstructed Serradura A playful take on the classic Portuguese dessert.br- 75 Chocolate A must-try for chocolate lovers who enjoy balanced sweetness.brbrDrinksbrThe cocktails are top-notch! I highly recommend Not a Screwdriver and KGFthey hit the right spot. Plus, the bartenders were kind enough to guide me in creating my own custom cocktail, which added a fun personal touch.brbrWhether youre planning a catch-up with friends, a family meal, or a romantic date night, Jamming Goat ticks all the boxes. The staff is friendly, attentive, and knowledgeable, making the entire experience seamless.brA perfect blend of flavors, creativity, and ambiance. Definitely worth a visit!

reviews.author: Harshit Udani

reviews.author: Pooja Barnwal
reviews.text: If youre looking for a fun spot in Indiranagar, Jamming Goat 3.0 is a great pick. Its got this awesome rooftop vibe with a mix of cozy booths and a lively bar area. The food here isnt your usual bar faretry the crispy broccoli poppers or the dimsums or the Charred Sweet Potato, which pack a punch. When it comes to drinks, their cocktails are next level! And for dessert, the Chocolate 75 is a rich, decadent choice. visit soon. br

reviews.author: N
reviews.text: A Culinary delight!brbrFrom the moment I stepped into Kopitiam lah, I knew I was in for a treat...inviting warmth that made me feel right at home. The atmosphere here is so soothing, it feels like an escape from the everyday.brbrThe menu offers a variety of dishes, each more tempting than the last. Chef Dsousa recommended an array of sumptuous dishes - each one was nothing short of a masterpiece. Every bite felt like a flavor explosion. The freshness of the ingredients and the artful presentation elevated the entire dining experience. Portion sizes were generous but never overwhelming, which made every dish feel like it was crafted with care.brbrAs impressive as the food was, the service truly stood out.You can tell when a team genuinely cares about your experience, and it was clear here. The staff anticipated our needs without us having to ask, making sure everything flowed seamlessly throughout the meal.brbrThe combination of mouthwatering cuisine, impeccable service, and a delightful atmosphere makes this place a must-visit. This is the kind of restaurant you keep coming back to. I cant wait to return!

reviews.author: Diana DBrass
reviews.text: This was a much long wait for me. I love Malaysian food and I couldnt wait to get my hands on some of Kopitiams delicious options. I ordered the Malaysian fried chicken, the beef red and and roti canai to go with the rending, the Kopi C and the Asian colada and let me tell you, it did not disappoint. The rendang was my absolute favourite. The flavour, the softness of the meat and the mild sweetness with a bit of heat, everything was up to the mark. I would def recommend you try it out with the roti canai. Im looking forward to heading there again and try their other dishes. Im sure theyll be as good if not better.

reviews.text: Decadent food, great ambience and good service.brbrMust try brKaya toastbrPandad French toastbrBaobrClassic milo brbrSlightly higher on the price spectrum it worth a visit.

reviews.author: Ragesh Radhakrishnan
reviews.text: Kopi in Malay translates to coffee, tiam is the Hokkien word for shop, while lah is a piece of popular flexible MalaysianSingaporean slangbrbrPut together we have Kopitiam Lah and right here in Namma BengalurubrbrThe history behind or the theme behind these coffee shops called Kopitiams in Malaysia is basically about a community space where the Chinese, Malay,  Indians in Malaysia all came together to swap stories over kopi, kaya toast fostering a sense of companionshipbrbrThe theme is pretty much translated to our own Indiranagar currently with some mouth watering dishes, meat luncheons, kaya toast and kopi

Chicken Satay- Was amazing and loved the crispy rice cakes that was served with it.brbr4- Nasi Lemak- This was served with chicken rendang and was absolutely delicious and I am definitely gonna go back for more. brbrHad an assortment of desserts and each of it tasted delicious.brbrCant wait to go back and try more!!

reviews.author: Sneha Kamath
reviews.text: Improved Feedback MessagebrSubject A Taste of Malaysia in Bangalore Kopitiam LahbrKopitiam Lah in Bangalore has truly brought a piece of Malaysia to India. With its diverse menu and authentic flavors, this restaurant offers a delightful culinary experience.brHighlightsbrKopi-C A classic Malaysian coffee that perfectly balances richness and sweetness.brCurry Puff A flaky pastry filled with savory curry that reminded me of my moms south Indian version potato samosas...br Asparagus Edamami Dumplings A healthier and delicious option, combining fresh asparagus and nutty edamame served with spiced coconut broth..br Curry Laksa A spicy and flavorful noodle soup with coconut milk that was a highlight of my meal.brWhile the tiramisu could have been improved with a slightly less eggy flavor and a smaller portion, the other dishes were exceptional.brA special thanks to the friendly and attentive staff, Achui, Kim, and Ofelia, who made my visit memorable.brOverall, Kopitiam Lah is a must-visit for anyone looking to experience authentic Malaysian cuisine in Bangalore.br

reviews.author: Archana
reviews.text: Visited Kopitiam Lah for breakfast and lunch over the last month and enjoyed it immensely. My husband is Malaysian, and this place takes him back to his childhood. Pls go expecting authentic Malay food, not the indian-ized or Singaporean versions that you see at all other asian restaurants in Bangalore. The char kway Teow is smoky and delicious, the satay is great, and the kuih is the perfect way to end each meal. Kopi-C is a must have, and if you want to try something different, get the carrot milk. The thick slabs of butter in the Kaya Toast offset the sweetness of the Kaya, and the hainanese omlette was a filling and delicious dish. Again, this is not your typical Pan-asian style food, so please expect authentic flavours that take you back to the wonderful cuisine of Malaysia.

reviews.author: Murthy
reviews.text: This is my second review of this place. The first one was a bad review for breakfast. This time around we went for lunch and it was excellent! All the dishes we ordered were absolutely delicious and I would definitely come back here for lunch. So skip breakfast time and come here for lunch. And dont miss the Rendang and the Roti Canai.

reviews.author: Radha Kashyap
reviews.text: An authentic place for Malay food is a win for me! The Kopi is excellent and made me nostalgic for my Singaporean college days, and the food is really fantastic. Starter portions were a bit small, but mains portions are generous! We got the Ayam nasi lemak, and the rice was super coconutty and perfect. Also got the mee hoon goreng, which was alright, but the seafood char kuey teow is my personal winner. PS, dont skip the bakery items, the egg tart and coffee custard bun are so good.

reviews.author: Abhishek Sen
reviews.text: When a new restaurant opens its doors on 12th main Indranagar...expectations go through the roof. Rumours...Anticipation and several social media waves later we finally managed to get a table at Kopitiam Lah! Chef Joonie Tans new kid on the block after her genre altering Lavonne. In short...expectations were exceeded and then some...highlights...br1. Chic yet rustic Malaysian cafe setting ... Crowded but clean and well managedbr2. Malaysian favorites like Kaya Toast, Malaysian fried noodles, Nasi Ayam, Char siu pork, Roti Canai and of course Beef Rendang didnt disappointbr3. A little loud but vibrant and super quick servicebrbrFor those coming for the first time...dont miss....the Tropical Tango drink or if you want to stick to the classics then Kopi C, the Char Siu Pork, Roti Canai paired with Beef Rendang, Chicken Satay with chunky peanut sauce...and finish it off with the Kopi TiramisubrLoved everything...cant wait to come back and sample the rest of the menu
